# License Plate Global Rules

- Use one shared normalization rule set for all plate outputs (detect, SR, history, export).
- Never display or persist raw model plate text directly when it violates plate format constraints.
- Normalize by plate type:
  - `blue/yellow/white/black`: 7 chars total (`province + city + 5`)
  - `green_small`: 8 chars total (`province + city + 6`, last char must be `D` or `F`)
- Allowed alphanumerics exclude `I` and `O`; unsupported chars must be replaced with `?`.
- Keep confidence and bbox as model outputs, but prioritize normalized text for UI and persistence.
- For motion-blur scenes, run a lightweight enhancement route before/alongside SR:
  - CLAHE
  - denoise (bilateral)
  - unsharp mask
- When multiple recognition routes are available, select by combined score:
  - confidence
  - format validity (fewer `?`, type-consistent length, green suffix check)
  - keep deterministic tie-breakers.

